WEBVTT

00:00:30.460 --> 00:00:33.542
Welcome to this edition of the vlog.

00:00:33.561 --> 00:00:35.582
We're out at our ocean studio.

00:00:35.622 --> 00:00:37.124
It's a lovely day.

00:00:37.384 --> 00:00:39.465
Beautiful weather has returned to the

00:00:39.524 --> 00:00:42.286
Virgin Islands and it's a pleasure to be

00:00:42.326 --> 00:00:45.246
able to share the ninth Mizmowr or psalm

00:00:45.767 --> 00:00:47.728
from Dowd, our King,

00:00:48.228 --> 00:00:51.209
both former and returning with you.

00:00:51.670 --> 00:00:52.270
It begins,

00:00:52.990 --> 00:00:56.573
to the enduring guide and everlasting

00:00:56.633 --> 00:00:58.493
director, ha natsach,

00:00:58.935 --> 00:01:00.875
the continuously glorious,

00:01:00.975 --> 00:01:06.641
majestic conductor in every endeavor over

00:01:06.680 --> 00:01:08.662
an unlimited duration of time.

00:01:09.722 --> 00:01:11.504
And this was written,

00:01:12.045 --> 00:01:13.846
at least the preamble now reads,

00:01:14.486 --> 00:01:17.069
upon the death of the son.

00:01:18.790 --> 00:01:21.533
al muwth, la ha ben.

00:01:22.893 --> 00:01:29.236
over a child dying a Mizmowr melody

00:01:29.537 --> 00:01:34.620
and lyrics of Dowd the beloved Dowd would

00:01:36.162 --> 00:01:42.706
experience the death of many children um

00:01:42.766 --> 00:01:46.968
the most egregious wasn't a son but a

00:01:47.049 --> 00:01:50.531
daughter uh well not excuse me it was

00:01:50.552 --> 00:01:52.673
I guess it was a son his um

00:01:55.436 --> 00:02:00.197
eldest son raped his daughter and his

00:02:01.697 --> 00:02:08.058
third born Absalon killed his firstborn a

00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:13.759
pretty tragic experience and also we have

00:02:13.780 --> 00:02:19.342
the uh the death of Bathsheba's uh son

00:02:20.542 --> 00:02:24.603
uh when uh I both

00:02:25.675 --> 00:02:30.056
she and Dowd engaged in a really awful

00:02:30.996 --> 00:02:34.056
relationship and it's the story that we

00:02:34.076 --> 00:02:37.736
have told over in the library studio

00:02:38.918 --> 00:02:43.579
pursuant to the last Mashal and so that

00:02:43.618 --> 00:02:47.680
was also a a tragic moment in his

00:02:47.759 --> 00:02:51.319
life and yes he had to suffer the

00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:54.420
death of a son but then uh that

00:02:55.508 --> 00:03:01.751
whole episode was so filled with angst and

00:03:01.890 --> 00:03:05.912
rebellion and hatred really towards God.

00:03:06.132 --> 00:03:07.771
That was a really bad episode.

00:03:08.292 --> 00:03:11.193
And then there's the death of Absalom who

00:03:11.332 --> 00:03:14.834
Dowd lamented to a great extent.

00:03:15.213 --> 00:03:17.674
Absalom is the one who killed his

00:03:17.713 --> 00:03:22.056
firstborn son and who did so to avenge

00:03:22.096 --> 00:03:23.876
the rape of his half sister.

00:03:25.222 --> 00:03:27.783
And then led a coup against Dowd,

00:03:28.283 --> 00:03:31.645
at which point when he was killed by

00:03:32.806 --> 00:03:35.489
Yoab, his lead general,

00:03:36.368 --> 00:03:39.570
Dowd cried bitterly over his death rather

00:03:39.631 --> 00:03:42.812
than celebrating the fact that a coup was

00:03:42.893 --> 00:03:43.112
over.

00:03:43.753 --> 00:03:46.975
Just a really an interesting period in

00:03:47.376 --> 00:03:48.796
Dowd's life,

00:03:49.037 --> 00:03:50.437
troubling period in Dowd's life.

00:03:51.808 --> 00:03:54.069
So we have four ways of looking at

00:03:54.129 --> 00:03:55.170
the death of a son.

00:03:55.230 --> 00:03:55.550
First,

00:03:55.631 --> 00:03:58.151
while the first of Dowd's physical bodies

00:03:58.231 --> 00:04:00.933
was long gone, having passed away,

00:04:01.514 --> 00:04:03.634
it was never relevant.

00:04:03.974 --> 00:04:06.515
His soul endures, and in the end,

00:04:06.537 --> 00:04:08.978
Dowd will return as the...

00:04:11.900 --> 00:04:12.961
In the physical realm,

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:16.423
serving Yah's right hand during the

00:04:16.442 --> 00:04:17.944
millennial celebration of Sukah,

00:04:17.963 --> 00:04:20.245
he'll return as Elyown,

00:04:20.766 --> 00:04:23.767
the very hand and influence of God.

00:04:25.228 --> 00:04:26.990
And so while Dowd is the son of

00:04:27.050 --> 00:04:30.531
God, he never died.

00:04:30.591 --> 00:04:34.173
So this cannot speak of him in that

00:04:34.254 --> 00:04:34.634
sense.

00:04:35.055 --> 00:04:37.276
His body died fulfilling Passover.

00:04:37.336 --> 00:04:39.218
His body died at the end of his

00:04:39.278 --> 00:04:39.658
first life.

00:04:40.384 --> 00:04:43.146
of three lives as he was seventy years

00:04:43.286 --> 00:04:43.526
old,

00:04:44.588 --> 00:04:47.928
but his body was meaningless to him in

00:04:48.029 --> 00:04:51.752
all of those situations.

00:04:51.812 --> 00:04:53.752
So at this point, a physical death,

00:04:56.564 --> 00:04:58.665
in a physical form anyway,

00:04:59.906 --> 00:05:01.927
is now entirely optional.

00:05:01.966 --> 00:05:04.809
If you want to part with your physical

00:05:04.829 --> 00:05:06.209
body, you can,

00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:08.850
according to the equation of E=MC²

00:05:08.911 --> 00:05:09.391
squared.

00:05:10.112 --> 00:05:10.891
That formula,

00:05:11.012 --> 00:05:13.853
you can go back and forth between being

00:05:13.913 --> 00:05:16.915
comprised of light and one that has some

00:05:17.216 --> 00:05:19.036
modicum of your body.

00:05:20.714 --> 00:05:23.357
light energy converted into matter.

00:05:23.997 --> 00:05:24.757
And ultimately,

00:05:25.478 --> 00:05:27.199
Dowd's going to be able to convert some

00:05:27.240 --> 00:05:28.661
of his light into energy,

00:05:28.961 --> 00:05:30.923
from energy into matter at any time of

00:05:30.963 --> 00:05:31.624
his choosing,

00:05:32.105 --> 00:05:34.526
making a corporeal form available when

00:05:34.586 --> 00:05:39.750
needed and while not otherwise a

00:05:39.790 --> 00:05:40.351
liability.

00:05:41.906 --> 00:05:42.005
Well,

00:05:42.026 --> 00:05:44.307
then there is Dowd's second Basar body,

00:05:44.346 --> 00:05:46.749
which was paramount importance because it

00:05:46.829 --> 00:05:49.750
served as the Passover lamb by dying.

00:05:50.430 --> 00:05:52.211
This body is long remembered,

00:05:52.252 --> 00:05:53.451
but long gone,

00:05:53.872 --> 00:05:56.314
having been incinerated before the sun

00:05:56.374 --> 00:06:01.596
rose on Matsah and set on Pesach in

00:06:01.656 --> 00:06:03.978
accordance with the Towrah's instructions.

00:06:04.738 --> 00:06:06.959
As for his soul, it was deployed,

00:06:07.040 --> 00:06:08.860
as we note, to Bethlehem.

00:06:10.322 --> 00:06:13.382
fulfill Matsah and carry our guilt into

00:06:13.403 --> 00:06:17.524
She'owl and then returned along with the

00:06:17.564 --> 00:06:22.867
Ruwach Qodesh at the completion of Matsah

00:06:23.387 --> 00:06:25.389
to enable the promise of Bikuwrym.

00:06:27.213 --> 00:06:27.333
Well,

00:06:27.353 --> 00:06:29.514
then there's also the children of Yisrael,

00:06:29.553 --> 00:06:31.675
the sons of Jacob and the heirs to

00:06:31.694 --> 00:06:32.235
the covenant.

00:06:32.255 --> 00:06:33.276
In all manner of speaking,

00:06:33.295 --> 00:06:35.396
they have died by the millions for having

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:36.697
rejected Yahowah.

00:06:37.358 --> 00:06:38.858
And there was a time when Yahowah said

00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:42.360
that the sword will never depart from you.

00:06:42.480 --> 00:06:43.560
And fourth, of course,

00:06:43.600 --> 00:06:45.942
was one of the great heartaches of life

00:06:46.523 --> 00:06:48.144
that really anyone can suffer.

00:06:48.831 --> 00:06:53.415
And Dowd would suffer it indeed at least

00:06:53.855 --> 00:06:55.416
three times that we know of,

00:06:56.076 --> 00:06:57.658
and that is the loss of a child.

00:06:57.677 --> 00:06:59.839
And as I say, Dowd lost three.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:03.382
His firstborn died on the eighth day.

00:07:04.603 --> 00:07:08.064
His secondborn was killed by his thirdborn

00:07:08.526 --> 00:07:10.547
so as to avenge the rape of his

00:07:10.586 --> 00:07:10.947
sister.

00:07:12.608 --> 00:07:15.009
and who was Dowd's eldest daughter.

00:07:15.069 --> 00:07:17.771
The third son was then killed for having

00:07:18.273 --> 00:07:20.473
led a coup d'etat against his father.

00:07:20.954 --> 00:07:22.795
I guess there was actually four because

00:07:22.836 --> 00:07:27.839
the fourth would be the son that he

00:07:27.920 --> 00:07:33.725
had through Bathsheba prior to Solomon

00:07:33.985 --> 00:07:35.386
being conceived and born.

00:07:37.233 --> 00:07:39.714
So this would have destroyed a lesser man,

00:07:39.754 --> 00:07:40.915
however, Dowd endured,

00:07:40.975 --> 00:07:43.237
largely because it drew him closer to Yah,

00:07:43.317 --> 00:07:43.858
eventually,

00:07:43.918 --> 00:07:46.000
as he understood the matters of life and

00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:46.321
death,

00:07:46.380 --> 00:07:49.103
enabling God's son to better empathize

00:07:49.124 --> 00:07:52.387
with his father over these rigors and the

00:07:52.507 --> 00:07:53.807
pain associated with them.

00:07:55.225 --> 00:07:59.026
So this is the, these are the lyrics.

00:07:59.245 --> 00:08:01.266
I express my appreciation.

00:08:01.687 --> 00:08:04.387
Yadah, this is with the hey ending.

00:08:05.307 --> 00:08:07.869
It's essentially yad, which means hand,

00:08:08.449 --> 00:08:13.411
and a female, feminine sense was yadah,

00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:16.692
or it can be perceived as associated with

00:08:18.432 --> 00:08:21.153
yada, knowing, the verb.

00:08:21.192 --> 00:08:21.353
So

00:08:22.228 --> 00:08:24.850
Yadah, I know, and therefore I am thankful,

00:08:25.389 --> 00:08:27.072
extolling what I understand.

00:08:27.612 --> 00:08:32.195
So yadah is either an active feminine

00:08:32.375 --> 00:08:34.456
influence on a hand,

00:08:35.697 --> 00:08:39.200
or it is derived from the verb yada,

00:08:39.379 --> 00:08:41.501
to know and be familiar with.

00:08:42.522 --> 00:08:45.465
It was written in the hifil Imperfect

00:08:45.524 --> 00:08:46.164
jussive,

00:08:46.764 --> 00:08:50.248
which means that it's a third-person

00:08:50.307 --> 00:08:51.288
expression of volition.

00:08:51.956 --> 00:08:52.558
To Yahowah,

00:08:54.403 --> 00:08:59.236
with my whole heart and my best judgment.

00:09:01.453 --> 00:09:03.975
I want to recount in writing, Saphar,

00:09:04.056 --> 00:09:06.256
I have chosen to quantify and record,

00:09:06.297 --> 00:09:07.658
to proclaim and inform,

00:09:07.697 --> 00:09:11.058
providing a permanent accounting of all of

00:09:11.119 --> 00:09:13.041
your wonderful deeds and amazing

00:09:13.100 --> 00:09:13.801
revelations.

00:09:13.880 --> 00:09:14.240
pala',

00:09:14.841 --> 00:09:16.402
your marvelous and astonishing

00:09:16.422 --> 00:09:17.082
accomplishments,

00:09:17.123 --> 00:09:19.724
your awe-inspiring and fulfilling acts,

00:09:19.744 --> 00:09:23.505
your extraordinary and distinguishing

00:09:23.566 --> 00:09:24.527
characteristics.

00:09:25.447 --> 00:09:25.687
Mizmowr

00:09:25.727 --> 00:09:27.849
lyrics to saying Psalm nine, one.

00:09:29.501 --> 00:09:31.682
So Dowd has risen to the occasion.

00:09:31.722 --> 00:09:33.523
He has affirmed the reason that Yahowah

00:09:33.582 --> 00:09:36.504
referred to him as his beloved son and

00:09:36.543 --> 00:09:38.844
his anointed Messiah, as well as a king.

00:09:38.923 --> 00:09:42.004
His thoughts and his words were devoted to

00:09:42.065 --> 00:09:43.904
sharing what he had come to know about

00:09:44.004 --> 00:09:44.426
Yahowah.

00:09:44.865 --> 00:09:47.086
He was engaged in the most important and

00:09:47.166 --> 00:09:49.407
beneficial mission in the universe.

00:09:49.966 --> 00:09:51.826
And considering the fact that we know that

00:09:52.427 --> 00:09:53.447
Dowd had, you know,

00:09:53.528 --> 00:09:56.327
forty eight reasonably good years and they

00:09:56.368 --> 00:09:57.168
were followed by

00:09:59.001 --> 00:09:59.241
Well,

00:09:59.322 --> 00:10:02.528
a period of at least fourteen years where

00:10:03.826 --> 00:10:06.768
some of that he was uh in the

00:10:06.908 --> 00:10:10.110
the depths of depression uh and I think

00:10:10.291 --> 00:10:12.511
certainly in the last four to six years

00:10:12.552 --> 00:10:15.254
of his life uh following an intervention

00:10:15.294 --> 00:10:19.498
he came back around so this was likely

00:10:19.778 --> 00:10:23.760
written either before Dowd fell into the

00:10:23.821 --> 00:10:28.063
depths of depression at fifty six years

00:10:28.183 --> 00:10:31.365
old or after he was

00:10:32.614 --> 00:10:34.294
released from it and recovered.

00:10:35.375 --> 00:10:36.275
One of those two.

00:10:38.216 --> 00:10:40.879
So particularly relevant,

00:10:40.938 --> 00:10:43.821
especially in the age of social media

00:10:43.860 --> 00:10:45.181
video presentations,

00:10:45.981 --> 00:10:47.082
which we're doing right now,

00:10:47.702 --> 00:10:50.264
Dowd was committed to the written word.

00:10:51.044 --> 00:10:53.725
No doubt he had a singer's and an

00:10:54.027 --> 00:10:55.888
orator's voice, but nevertheless,

00:10:56.408 --> 00:10:58.249
he wrote the lyrics of his songs so

00:10:58.288 --> 00:11:01.051
that they would endure the test of time.

00:11:01.940 --> 00:11:02.519
Further,

00:11:02.539 --> 00:11:04.760
Dowd was the lead participant throughout

00:11:04.880 --> 00:11:07.822
the unification of Israel and during the

00:11:07.841 --> 00:11:08.942
fulfillment of the Miqra'.

00:11:10.302 --> 00:11:13.965
He was always more than just a prophetic

00:11:13.985 --> 00:11:14.445
witness,

00:11:14.705 --> 00:11:16.085
although he was extraordinary in that

00:11:16.144 --> 00:11:16.365
role.

00:11:17.566 --> 00:11:20.267
When he chronicles the events transpiring

00:11:20.527 --> 00:11:22.748
during Pesach and thirty-three CE,

00:11:23.148 --> 00:11:26.529
he knows what he is talking about because

00:11:26.570 --> 00:11:27.649
he endured that pain.

00:11:29.635 --> 00:11:31.177
So this reads, I will rejoice.

00:11:31.336 --> 00:11:33.379
I will of my own volition delight,

00:11:33.438 --> 00:11:35.980
and I will be elated, even jubilant,

00:11:36.041 --> 00:11:37.662
expressing my admiration,

00:11:38.503 --> 00:11:39.884
celebrating with you.

00:11:40.224 --> 00:11:42.505
And I want to sing to your godly

00:11:42.566 --> 00:11:42.885
name.

00:11:44.183 --> 00:11:48.005
Mizmowr Psalm nine two notes clearly

00:11:48.787 --> 00:11:51.307
embracing Yahowah at this point in his

00:11:51.347 --> 00:11:51.607
life.

00:11:51.668 --> 00:11:53.068
It's either, as I say before,

00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:58.773
he descended into the alcohol driven

00:11:58.832 --> 00:12:03.134
depression that spawned the ugliness of

00:12:03.154 --> 00:12:06.376
the Bathsheba incident,

00:12:07.197 --> 00:12:10.198
or it is after he recovered from it

00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:12.821
that he would have been in this mindset.

00:12:14.312 --> 00:12:14.432
Now,

00:12:14.491 --> 00:12:15.712
one of the things that I've come to

00:12:15.793 --> 00:12:18.933
love about our king is that he was

00:12:18.994 --> 00:12:22.296
not bashful in expressing his feelings.

00:12:22.495 --> 00:12:25.596
As frustrated as he often was with his

00:12:25.658 --> 00:12:28.499
fellow man, and sometimes even with God,

00:12:29.379 --> 00:12:34.221
he came to endure by loving Yahowah.

00:12:34.381 --> 00:12:38.703
And for all of these wonderful statements

00:12:38.783 --> 00:12:39.703
of that love,

00:12:40.985 --> 00:12:43.046
we know that there was mutual admiration

00:12:45.532 --> 00:12:48.115
So as we all know,

00:12:48.394 --> 00:12:49.716
in the Eighty-Ninth Mizmowr,

00:12:50.736 --> 00:12:56.202
Dowd was said upon Yahowah's return that he

00:12:56.243 --> 00:12:57.845
would be Elyown,

00:12:58.625 --> 00:13:01.028
essentially all things pertaining to the

00:13:01.087 --> 00:13:02.649
hand and influence of God.

00:13:05.798 --> 00:13:08.821
This was set in comparison to all of

00:13:08.841 --> 00:13:10.982
the most exalted of the earth.

00:13:11.703 --> 00:13:13.865
And here we find further affirmation that

00:13:14.326 --> 00:13:17.928
Elyown is one of Yahowah's titles.

00:13:18.649 --> 00:13:22.552
Dowd's use is consistent with what we find

00:13:23.373 --> 00:13:24.594
actually throughout the Towrah.

00:13:25.615 --> 00:13:26.255
Most people,

00:13:27.236 --> 00:13:29.557
especially at the loss of a child,

00:13:29.597 --> 00:13:29.899
would say,

00:13:30.791 --> 00:13:33.412
either blame God and be embittered towards

00:13:33.432 --> 00:13:36.212
him or believe that for this to occur,

00:13:36.873 --> 00:13:38.793
there must be no God at all.

00:13:39.874 --> 00:13:42.695
And yet, Dowd searched for and found,

00:13:42.774 --> 00:13:43.575
then embraced,

00:13:44.294 --> 00:13:47.436
the reason behind death and the solution

00:13:47.475 --> 00:13:49.177
for it that God had provided.

00:13:50.937 --> 00:13:52.456
We don't have to die when we die.

00:13:52.817 --> 00:13:53.898
Our souls can live on.

00:13:55.250 --> 00:13:55.370
Now,

00:13:55.389 --> 00:13:57.351
I've come to see life in this way,

00:13:57.631 --> 00:13:58.272
Dowd's way,

00:13:58.773 --> 00:14:00.734
which is one of the reasons I find

00:14:01.173 --> 00:14:03.375
his life and lyrics so illuminating,

00:14:03.436 --> 00:14:04.236
so inspiring.

00:14:05.277 --> 00:14:08.320
With the proper attitude and with sound

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:10.701
thinking, we can learn and grow from,

00:14:10.721 --> 00:14:12.503
well, every experience,

00:14:12.743 --> 00:14:14.303
as eventually did Dowd,

00:14:15.085 --> 00:14:16.686
particularly the most difficult one.

00:14:17.894 --> 00:14:20.635
Now, according to many scholars,

00:14:20.937 --> 00:14:23.538
having respect for Yahowah's name precludes

00:14:23.618 --> 00:14:25.198
it from being spoken.

00:14:26.058 --> 00:14:29.100
And yet, how would that even be possible?

00:14:29.581 --> 00:14:31.422
Since no one had greater respect for

00:14:31.461 --> 00:14:32.701
Yahowah than Dowd,

00:14:33.523 --> 00:14:35.624
he routinely sang it aloud.

00:14:37.105 --> 00:14:38.686
Why would he have written it into the

00:14:38.706 --> 00:14:42.167
lyrics if it would serve no purpose?

00:14:42.847 --> 00:14:44.467
Do you think that God would have told

00:14:44.548 --> 00:14:44.908
us that

00:14:45.875 --> 00:14:52.600
Yahowah's name was too sacred to pronounce.

00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:55.821
If that were actually the case,

00:14:55.841 --> 00:14:56.822
do you think he would tell us,

00:14:57.322 --> 00:14:58.322
my name is Yahowah,

00:14:58.342 --> 00:14:59.543
but don't you dare say it?

00:15:00.663 --> 00:15:02.465
If you say it, you might mispronounce it,

00:15:02.485 --> 00:15:03.706
and that would really upset me.

00:15:03.885 --> 00:15:04.926
No, he doesn't say that at all.

